which cc
```

Example output:

```
/usr/bin/cc
```

Now check if it is a **symbolic link**:

```
ls -l /usr/bin/cc
```

Example result:

```
lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root 20 Jun 10 12:00 /usr/bin/cc -> /etc/alternatives/cc
```

This means:

```
cc → /etc/alternatives/cc
```

---

## 3. Linux Alternatives System

Linux distributions (like Ubuntu/Debian) use the **alternatives system** to choose default programs.

```
/etc/alternatives/cc
```

Check it:

```
ls -l /etc/alternatives/cc
```

Example:

```
